data.enText: carrying a load; full and heavy

data.chText: 她端着装满食物的托盘走进了房间。
data.enText: She came into the room carrying a loaded tray.
full of a particular thing, quality or meaning
acting either as an advantage or a disadvantage to sb/sth in a way that is unfair
a system that is loaded in favour of the young (= gives them an advantage)
having more meaning than you realize at first and intended to make you think in a particular way

data.chText: 这是个带有圈套的问题，还是不作评论为好。
data.enText: It was a loaded question and I preferred not to comment.

means: 大量给予(尤指得携带的东西)

tr: (of statements or questions) charged with associative significance and often meant to mislead or influence
having an abundant supply of money or possessions of value

value.def: A loaded question or word has more meaning or purpose than it appears to have, because the person who uses it hopes it will cause people to respond in a particular way.

example.tran: 言外有言的“性别歧视者”一词

value.tran: （问题或词语）哄骗性的，意味深长的，另有所指的

value.def: If something is loaded with a particular characteristic, it has that characteristic to a very great degree.

example.ex: The President's visit is loaded with symbolic significance...
example.tran: 总统之行充满象征性意义。

example.ex: The phrase is loaded with irony.

gramarinfo.label: usu v-link ADJ, usu ADJ <l>with</l> n

value.def: If you say that something is loaded in favour of someone, you mean it works unfairly to their advantage. If you say it is loaded against them, you mean it works unfairly to their disadvantage.

example.ex: The press is loaded in favour of this present government...
The article was heavily loaded against Morrissey.
example.tran: 文章对莫里西非常不利。

example.ex: ...very loaded experiments carried out by General Bobby Marshall.
example.tran: 博比·马歇尔将军搞的有严重倾向性的试验

gramarinfo.label: usu v-link ADJ <l>in favour of/against</l> n

value.tran: （不公平地）有…倾向的，有…偏向的，倒向…的
